Text.Value: Got a death wish, have you? Contract came from a wizard in Baldur's Gate.
One fight just ended, and now you're picking another? Relax.
What'll you do now?
Tell you what, though: look me up if you're ever in the city. I owe you a pint.
Mission accomplished, I guess.
Head back to Baldur's Gate. Better empty-handed than dead. I'm done with this shite.
Strangely, I can almost hear the Chionthar's rush. How far are we?
Home sweet home. How far down the Chionthar are we?
At least we agree on that.
Too little, too late.
Please. You were begging me to open the gate. Anything to save yourself, you coward.
STOP OR I'LL BASH YOUR SKULLS TOGETHER MYSELF.
Heh, don't thank me. I'll be well on my way to Baldur's Gate when you die.
He's right. We should scram while we can.
She's right. We should scram while we can.
They're right. We should scram while we can.
Tough hitter like you might last there. Maybe.
*With a thunk, the armoured man collapses - unconscious.*
Nobody forced him to go with us - he insisted. And when things got tough, he couldn't keep up. Simple as that.
Forgive me, sister. I... forgot myself.
Forgive me, brother. I... forgot myself.
Forgive me, cousin. I... forgot myself.

EditorData.AnimationTags: CMitchell:, ZEVLOR looks down at his clenched fists and then relaxes
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Looks from his hands to you.
EditorData.NodeContext: Speaking to a fellow tiefling. Ashamed at what he's done and that he's let you down.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: player punches Zevlor on the jaw, knocking him down
EditorData.SFXTags: Punch impact, fall to the ground

Text.Value: Calm down, both of you, before I put you down.
Stop squealing like hatchlings or settle this matter in blood.
God forbid you risk your precious tail. But I shouldn't be surprised.
He's human - malice comes as naturally as breathing. Just show him you're the better man.
Thanks. I do my best.
You can cough up my payment any time now.
Want me to knock you both out? Or would you prefer to skip the broken bones and just calm down?
Maybe I could take that job off your hands, if you've lost your appetite for it.
I told him he wasn't getting so much as a sniff of the reward, but he tagged along anyhow.
Enough. Squabbling is pointless. The goblins have found us.
Leave.
You put him in a bind, showing up like that. And he did try to open the gate.
You led them straight to us. And you let them take the druid, too. Unbelievable!

EditorData.NodeContext: He's completely lost his temper at this point. Words are spat out.

Text.Value: I'd give you the map and wish you a happy funeral, but my mate Brian kept hold of it like his own todger. Goblins made short of the fat old chunk.
Druid? Those goblins didn't take any prisoners.
Right. Lead goblins here, then leave the rest of us to fight them off. You coward.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Rolls his eyes in exasperation at the player and then points at Aradin.
EditorData.NodeContext: Disgusted with Aradin. Oozing with derision.

Text.Value: Stand back and watch.
Shut it, horns. I'd be lying dead next to the goblins if you'd stalled any longer.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Points at Zevlor on first phrase - violent gesture. Emphasis on 'I'd' since he's responding to Zevlor talking of the dead
EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to turn the tide. Accusation is strong in his voice,

Text.Value: I'd rather face another round of goblins than stay in this pit.
So you knocked him out cold instead. Clever.
More violence won't bring back those you lost. Stop and think.
Enough.
We've got a contract to track down some relic, and he wanted in on the job. Eyes lit up when he heard about it.
He's either diggin' latrines or boilin' in a cookpot by now.
Where there's one goblin, there's ten. I'm leaving before the horde shows up.
What chewed you up and spit you out?
Shoulda done that a long time ago. Arrogant prick had it out for me from day one.
The goblins have found us. No doubt, the beasts will be back.
There are children here, you fool!

EditorData.NodeContext: Absolutely furious.  He and his crew nearly died. Right in Zevlor's face.

Text.Value: Damn. Didn't expect a devilkin to turn on one of their own.
Damn. You knocked him clean out.
No one leaves my people out cold.
Take a swing at the tiefling.
You're not locals, then. Who runs this place?
Keep that luck, mate. You'll need it.
And who the hell are you again?!

RuleGroup.RuleString: FIGHTER or PALADIN or RANGER or ROGUE

Text.Value: I've seen much bloodier battles than this. Consider yourselves lucky.
Somewhere in my noxious blood, Baldur's Gate is calling to me.
Ain't stayin' around here with horns knocked cold out. Rest of these devils'll be out for blood.
Ain't stayin' around here with this'n knocked cold out. Here's hopin' they'll grant mercy to one of their own.
Only way he'd shut that hole under his nose.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: In one swift move, the armoured man's fist makes contact with a sickening crunch.
EditorData.SFXTags: Punch impact, fall to the ground

Text.Value: You're right. There's too much at stake.
Pull your claws in, under-elf.
Ah, 'devilkin'. Certainly never heard that one before. Creative.
What was important enough to drag a druid out of his grove?
You lads gonna settle this or are you just ranting like a couple of derro?
How about we cool those hot tempers and talk this through calmly?
*He acts before you can intervene...*

EditorData.AnimationTags: CMitchell:, PLAYER CINE_React_Fail, ZEVLOR deftly sidesteps the punch. [DUPE]
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player starts to react, but is cut off

Text.Value: What's it gonna take to shut you up, horns?
Got himself nabbed by gobbos - same ones what chased us here.
Worried about your precious hides, the both of you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Seething with arrogance and a superiority complex.

Text.Value: What even is this relic?
Best of luck. Hope your next contract's more fruitful.
It's a druids' grove - fella in charge went by the name Halsin. He ain't here anymore, though.
Ah, backstabbing. This feels just like home.
Thanks.
Foulbloods ain't known for courage.
Spare me the chilling warnings and just tell me where I can find this thing.
We have people to protect. Let us work towards that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Anger has mainly disappeared. Disgusted with himself but trying to lead. Still arrogant.

Text.Value: If you want me to take both of you down, I will. Otherwise, knock it off.
There are cut-throats there who'll leave you empty-handed and dead, just so you know.
Show some respect! This man saved your pathetic life.
Show some respect! This woman saved your pathetic life.
Show some respect! If not for them, your pathetic life would be over.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The tiefling lands a glancing blow across the man's temple.
The player punches Aradin, Aradin gets knocked out
EditorData.SFXTags: Punch impact, fall to the ground

Text.Value: I'm out.
Watch yourself. I'm out.
The Gate will take you for all you're worth with a smile. I remember it now. My kind of place.
The Gate will take you for all you're worth with a smile. At least goblins rob you proper.
Aradin Beno. Leader of the Beno Boys. Adventurers for hire 'n all.
He was right, though. Coming back to this hellhole was a mistake no amount of gold can put right.
I prefer to settle matters with my own hands.
You're outta luck. Halsin - druid who runs this place - knew his stuff. But he ain't here anymore.
My gods, you're a coward.
Think he's got an apprentice running around somewheres, though. Nadine? Natalie? Something like that.
My duty is to this camp.
What would be nice is a healer. Do me a favour and point me to one.
We was running for our lives.

EditorData.NodeContext: Exasperated. Thinks Zevlor is just being unreasonable.

Text.Value: Leave.
*You see the tiefling's jaw clench. He's about to erupt.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: CMitchell:, ZEVLOR _SquareUp_Start and _Loop, PLAYER [Look-at Gesture] SizeUp.
EditorData.NodeContext: High tension. About to rear back and punch Aradin
EditorData.VFXTags: Casts spell that could kill Aradin (consider cutting)

Text.Value: Far enough that I ain't sure we'll make it back in one piece. And before you ask, I ain't takin' tag-alongs.
It's called the Nightsong. Supposed to be hidden under the temple where the goblins jumped us.
Aim a blow at the human.
Aim a blow at the human, trying to knock him flat on his back.
Somebody had to. Just tell me what this place is - I feel magic in the trees.
I didn't do it for your praise. Just tell me what this place is.
We lost him back at the ruins - whole place is crawling with gobbos.
Leave.
Nice.
Tell that to the dead at the gate.
If you head that way, you'll likely smell 'em or hear their drums before you see 'em.
Well, I didn't ask for any goddamn help.
That's... that, I suppose.

EditorData.NodeContext: He's happy but it's outside his zone of comfort (being a teacher)

Text.Value: Let him speak.
I'm sure you think so. Now point me to a healer.
No points for effort. Care to tell me what this place is?
And you left him where, exactly?
*The human's eye twitches. He's about to blow.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: CMitchell:, ARADIN [REUSE] _SquareUp_Start and _Loop, PLAYER [Look-at Gesture] SizeUp.
EditorData.NodeContext: High tension moment. Violence is about to erupt.

Text.Value: Stuff your payment. I didn't ask for any goddamn help.
True enough. City's got pubs, though, don't it?
We need to pack up and leave. Immediately.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He turns and prepares to leave.

Text.Value: Gobbos are holed up in the temple ruins out west of here - last I saw Halsin, he was right in the thick of 'em.
All I've got's the contract. It'll show you where we turned back, if you feel like dying.
But look, if you're itching to meet Kelemvor, I won't stop you.
Before you go, let me see that contract. Maybe I'll fare better than you did.
But all that gold ain't gonna do you any good if you're too cold to spend it.
He trusted you.
If I knew that, I wouldn't be back here with half my crew gone.
Baldur's Gate is legendary. I've never clapped eyes on it, personally.
Relic's supposedly hidden underneath a temple 'round these parts, and he'll pay gobloads for it.
Got a healer in your crew?
Leave.
Look me up if you're ever in the city. I owe you a pint.
Haven't seen any signs of a city in these parts. How far is it?
What's unbelievable is how we beat the goblins! You're both heroes.

Synopsis: After the goblins' raid on Halsin's camp, the tiefling leader berates the adventurers for causing trouble. The situation can escalate until one leader is knocked out, or it can be descalated with the aid of the player.
